# Bead browserplex-7p0.4 — DOCS

**No shipped user-facing docs change in this bead.** Rationale:
- The `bp` command surface is now ergonomic, but the installable `bp` bin + the README "CLI usage"
  section are owned by bead **.7 (Docs + packaging)** — which already has a note to document `bp`
  and fix the stale `dist/index.js` install paths. Documenting CLI usage here (before the bin
  exists / `bp` is on PATH) would be premature and immediately reworked by .7.
- `bp --help` / `bp <command> --help` are self-documenting in the meantime.
- The MCP server surface is unchanged.

Command-table design is recorded in `docs/plans/process/browserplex-7p0.4-PLAN.md`.
